The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Tuesday, March 30, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 A crucial round of the IFA-Subhas Bhowmick saga will take place on Tuesday evening. The East Bengal coach, handed a two-year suspension (in effect from May) for derogatory remarks against the state body, will get a chance to defend himself before the IFAs governing body. Though some see this as the first step towards the punishment being reduced, much will depend on how the coach presents his case.				 																																																	 Nadia district emerged champions in the mens and womens sections of the fifth inter-non-government college state athletic championship which concluded on Sunday. Debashish Das and Kamaluddin Mondal of Nadia were adjudged best in the mens section, while Sutapa Das of Malda was best among women. 				 																																																	 Calcutta Port Trust have won the first division basketball league title following their 70-62 victory over Eastern Railway. Arunava Auddy netted 24 points for the winners while Subhas Bhattacharya scored 20. 				 																																																	HOCKEY: Beighton Cup qualifiers: Eastern Railway vs Muslim Institute (CCFC); BSF North Bengal vs CLW (East Bengal). Matches from 3 pm.
